commit.message:
Can't create lock/pid files in common dir

Due to permission issues if two different users on same system.
Should put lock and pid files in common directory

Ensure that configuration file is a file, not dir

Also clean up imports as per isort.
Change from flake8 to ruff

Add note that does not work for touchscreen

Re issue #345.

Remove requirement to use make to install/upgrade

Some users may not have make installed and we are not really using it
anyhow as it just runs ./libinput-gestures-setup install so user may as
well run it directly.
Improve words for trouble-shooting gesture events

Improve example for changing audio volume

Reference: issue #340
Improve implementation of unexpand_user()
Minimum Python version now 3.6
Add a badge
Enable vermin print min version
Update description of systemd service

Add note to conf about command not parsed by shell

Re issue #337.
Minor update to Makefile

Depreciate systemd user service option

Starting as a systemd user service is simply unreliable so this commit
depreciates that option in the README although it is still available as
an option in the startup code.

Remove need for Python packaging library

Fixes issue #327.

Parsing of gesture messages should be less fragile

Fixes issue #326.
Use packaging.version instead of distutils.version
Add example hold on gesture
Add hold gestures for libinput 1.19

Add note about potential systemd start problem

Re issue #305.

Ensure required systemd target is available

Re issue #305, we should check if the systemd target we require is
actually available before allowing installation as a systemd user
service.
Add shell script to facilitate dummy testing
Should reload systemd if service file has changed
Ensure all systemd start links are removed
Change setup program to accept multiple commands
Fix start/stop logic
Remove redundant newline

Add status output to list option

Also calculate version hash based on the main and setup programs.
